column1: # The results of 100 simulations using each of EvolvAGene [36] and INDELible [37], aligned with Clustal [2], MUSCLE [3] and Mafft with local and global settings [4].
# Number of positions: total number of positions in the alignment
# CIAlign_stringency: parameter settings as listed in Supplementary Table 1 (None means without running CIAlign).
# Correct_Pairs_Removed: the proportion of correctly aligned pairs of residues in the test alignment which are removed by CIAlign
# Nt_Removed, Gaps_Removed, Positions_Removed: proportion of non-gap positions, gap positions, all positions removed by CIAlign, respectively
# Consensus_NW_Score: Needleman-Wunsch score for a consensus sequence generated from the alignment compared to the input sequence to EvolvAGene
# Consensus_Alignment_Length, length of alignment of the consensus sequence with the input sequence
# Consensus_Percentage_Similarity: percentage similarity between the consensus sequence and the input sequence
# Consensus_Percentage_Identity: percentage identity between the consensus sequence and the input sequence

# Robinson-Foulds_Distance, Normalised_Robinson-Foulds_Distance, Quartet_Divergence: Robinson-Foulds distance [34], Normalised Robinson-Foulds distance [34] and Quartet divergence [35] between the tree generated based on this alignment and the true tree generated by the simulation software.
